---
import Layout from '@/layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout>
<main class="flex-grow flex flex-col items-center justify-center py-section px-6 md:px-12 w-full max-w-6xl mx-auto">
        <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
            
            <!-- General Questions -->
            <section class="mb-xl">
                <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-lg">
                    <span class="material-symbols-outlined text-brand-red">help</span>
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold uppercase tracking-tight">General Questions</h2>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-white rounded-3xl border border-outline-variant overflow-hidden shadow-sm">
                    <details class="faq-item group">
                        <summary class="flex justify-between items-center p-lg cursor-pointer hover:bg-surface-container-low transition-colors">
                            <span class="font-bold text-on-surface">What is Typpy?</span>
                            <span class="material-symbols-outlined expand-icon text-outline">expand_more</span>
                        </summary>
                        <div class="px-lg pb-lg text-on-surface-variant leading-relaxed">
                            Typpy is a gamified typing platform designed to improve speed, accuracy, and real-world typing ability through interactive challenges and adaptive learning.
                        </div>
                    </details>
                    <details class="faq-item group">
                        <summary class="flex justify-between items-center p-lg cursor-pointer hover:bg-surface-container-low transition-colors">
                            <span class="font-bold text-on-surface">How is Typpy different from other typing websites?</span>
                            <span class="material-symbols-outlined expand-icon text-outline">expand_more</span>
                        </summary>
                        <div class="px-lg pb-lg text-on-surface-variant">
                            <p class="mb-sm">Most platforms specialize in one area (Typing.com for lessons, Monkeytype for customization). Typpy combines:</p>
                            <ul class="list-disc ml-6 space-y-1">
                                <li>Learning + gaming + analytics</li>
                                <li>Real-world typing scenarios (emails, code)</li>
                                <li>Adaptive difficulty that grows with you</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </details>
                    <details class="faq-item group">
                        <summary class="flex justify-between items-center p-lg cursor-pointer hover:bg-surface-container-low transition-colors">
                            <span class="font-bold text-on-surface">Is Typpy for beginners or advanced typists?</span>
                            <span class="material-symbols-outlined expand-icon text-outline">expand_more</span>
                        </summary>
                        <div class="px-lg pb-lg text-on-surface-variant">
                            <p><strong>Beginners:</strong> Guided progression similar to structured curricula. <br>
                            <strong>Intermediate:</strong> Targeted improvement of weak patterns. <br>
                            <strong>Advanced:</strong> Optimization and competitive high-speed play.</p>
                        </div>
                    </details>
                </div>
            </section>

            <!-- Learning & Science -->
            <section class="mb-xl">
                <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-lg">
                    <span class="material-symbols-outlined text-brand-red">science</span>
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold uppercase tracking-tight">Learning & Improvement</h2>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-white rounded-3xl border border-outline-variant overflow-hidden shadow-sm">
                    <details class="faq-item group">
                        <summary class="flex justify-between items-center p-lg cursor-pointer hover:bg-surface-container-low transition-colors">
                            <span class="font-bold text-on-surface">Why do I type fast in tests but slow in real life?</span>
                            <span class="material-symbols-outlined expand-icon text-outline">expand_more</span>
                        </summary>
                        <div class="px-lg pb-lg text-on-surface-variant">
                            Many tests use repeated common words and lack punctuation. This creates a false sense of speed. Typpy uses real-world text like emails and code to ensure your skills translate to your actual work.
                        </div>
                    </details>
                    <details class="faq-item group">
                        <summary class="flex justify-between items-center p-lg cursor-pointer hover:bg-surface-container-low transition-colors">
                            <span class="font-bold text-on-surface">What is “touch typing” and why is it important?</span>
                            <span class="material-symbols-outlined expand-icon text-outline">expand_more</span>
                        </summary>
                        <div class="px-lg pb-lg text-on-surface-variant">
                            Touch typing means typing without looking at the keyboard. Studies show it boosts speed to ~61 WPM (vs ~39 WPM when looking down) and significantly reduces cognitive load.
                        </div>
                    </details>
                    <details class="faq-item group">
                        <summary class="flex justify-between items-center p-lg cursor-pointer hover:bg-surface-container-low transition-colors">
                            <span class="font-bold text-on-surface">Why do I hit a plateau?</span>
                            <span class="material-symbols-outlined expand-icon text-outline">expand_more</span>
                        </summary>
                        <div class="px-lg pb-lg text-on-surface-variant">
                            Common reasons include repeating easy tests, lack of specific feedback, and avoiding difficult keys. Typpy breaks plateaus by detecting your "weak keys" and forcing smarter practice.
                        </div>
                    </details>
                </div>
            </section>

